  "texts": [
    "When asked about a TN sample (Fig. 1), the model correctly identifies the network flow as a DNS query.",
    "However, it inaccurately claims the source IP address is from China, whereas it is actually from Japan, and misidentifies the destination address as being in the USA, although it belongs to the University of New South Wales (UNSW), the dataset's creator.",
    "Despite these errors, the LLM correctly identifies the byte size range of all packets in the flow as typical for a DNS query.",
    "These inaccuracies highlight the LLM's tendency to hallucinate or generate incorrect information, particularly regarding geographical locations.On a TP case, the LLM mistakenly states that protocol 139 corresponds to the NetBIOS protocol, whereas it corresponds to the Host Identity Protocol.",
    "Its confusion is evident as NetBIOS uses port 139."
  ],
